-- MOVES-JP Morgan's top retail banking lawyer leaves - Bloomberg
-- 
-- Tue Aug 05, 2014 01:52AM EDT
-- None



Aug 5 (Reuters) - JPMorgan Chase & Co's <JPM.N> general counsel for retail banking business, Matthew Biben, has left the company after three years, Bloomberg reported, citing a person familiar with the move.

Jill Centella, who heads global litigation for the New York-based bank, was appointed the acting general counsel for its consumer banking operations in June, Bloomberg said. (http://bloom.bg/1nmW70f) It was not immediately clear where Biben was moving. Biben has earlier worked with the Bank of New York Mellon <BK.N> and the U.S. Attorney's office for the Southern District of New York.